  "prompt": "What is meant by monopolistic competition?",
  "response": "Monopolistic competition is a type of market structure where many producers offer products or services that are similar, but not perfect substitutes. In this type of market, firms have some degree of market power, allowing them to set their own prices, but they still face competition from other firms offering similar products. Each firm in a monopolistic competition tries to differentiate its product through branding, quality, features, or other methods, in order to create a perception of uniqueness and gain a competitive advantage. Examples of industries that operate under monopolistic competition include restaurants, clothing, and personal care products.",
